    "body": "With the new structured logging framework changes, spark is not using `org.slf4j.Logger` and `org.slf4j.LoggerFactory` directly,  and instead using `org.apache.spark.internal.SparkLogger` and `org.apache.spark.internal.SparkLoggerFactory` from java code.\r\n\r\nWe use the `org.slf4j.Logger*` classes in: GpuSparkBatchQueryScan.java, BaseDataReader.java, GpuMultiFileBatchReader.java, GpuParquetScan.java. Spark has moved also to \"ban\" using the slf4j classes using check style, which shouldn't affect us, but fyi.\r\n\r\nI think we should try and use the new logging if we can and it means shimming it because these are new classes.",
